techmeme.title: Australia plans to introduce legislation that would ban children under 16 from using social media, not exempting those already with accounts or parental consent (Maani Truu/ABC)
Take-Two reports Q2 net bookings up 2% YoY to $1.47B, vs. $1.43B est., net revenue up 4% to $1.35B, and sells its Private Division label to an unnamed buyer (Zaheer Kachwala/Reuters)
Bumble reports Q3 revenue down 0.7% YoY to $273.6M, vs. $271.9M est., its first quarterly sales drop since going public in 2021, and 4.3M total paying users (Priyanka.G/Reuters)
JPMorgan rebrands its Onyx blockchain unit as Kinexys and plans to add on-chain foreign exchange capabilities as early as Q1 2025, starting with USD and EUR (Krisztian Sandor/CoinDesk)
CrowdStrike agrees to acquire Tel Aviv-based Adaptive Shield, which offers cloud security for SaaS apps; sources say CrowdStrike will pay ~$300M for the company (Meir Orbach/CTech)
